---
title: GITPLC — GitHub Issues as PLC config + alarm log
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Sen as Sensor / Ring
    participant Mas as SCADA Master
    participant Tdb as Tag DB
    participant Sdb as State DB
    participant Gh as GitHub repo<br/>teslasolar/GITPLC
    participant Op as Operator HMI

    Note over Gh: config-as-code via labelled issues<br/>gitplc-config plc-alarm

    Op->>Gh: open issue PLC CONFIG<br/>label gitplc-config
    Gh-->>Mas: webhook config changed
    Mas->>Tdb: hydrate UDT thresholds

    Op->>Gh: open issue EQUIPMENT<br/>seed instances
    Gh-->>Mas: register devices
    Mas->>Tdb: create instance tags

    loop scan period
        Sen->>Mas: ingest PV quality ts
        Mas->>Tdb: write value
        Mas->>Sdb: maybe transition state
    end

    Sen->>Mas: PV crosses HiHi
    Mas->>Sdb: alarm.ACTIVE
    Mas->>Gh: create issue plc-alarm<br/>title PT-101 HIGH-HIGH
    Gh-->>Op: notification
    Op->>Gh: comment ACK PV=97.2
    Gh-->>Mas: comment webhook
    Mas->>Sdb: alarm.ACKED

    Sen->>Mas: PV back in band
    Mas->>Sdb: alarm.CLEARED
    Mas->>Gh: comment CLEARED close issue

    Note over Mas,Gh: every state edge writes a comment<br/>full audit trail in git history
